<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Apparel2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Apparel,</orth> vb., to dress: <cit><quote>I will a. them all in one livery,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 80</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. thy head,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 104</bibl></cit> (it is Armado that speaks). <cit><quote>and are --ed thus, like Muscovites,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.120" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 120</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 76</bibl>. To put in a showy dress: <cit><quote>a. vice like virtue's harbinger,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 12</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.229" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 229</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 12</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>